Everybody else tires and they just get stronger.
其他人都累了, 他们却越战越勇

933
00:58:19,670 --> 00:58:21,410
That's the third time they beat the varsity squad.
这是他们第三次击败校队

934
00:58:21,480 --> 00:58:22,640
Maybe next time.
也许下次就输了

935
00:58:24,130 --> 00:58:25,810
I just think it's too big of a risk.
我只是觉得风险太大了

936
00:58:26,150 --> 00:58:28,940
Poughkeepsie is more than just the championship this year.
波基普西今年不仅仅是冠军赛

937
00:58:28,970 --> 00:58:30,130
It's for the Olympics.
也是奥运会选拔赛

938
00:58:30,180 --> 00:58:31,410
I know what the race means, Tom.
我知道比赛意味着什么, 汤姆

939
00:58:31,470 --> 00:58:33,050
Experience counts for something in big races.
在大型比赛中, 经验很重要

940
00:58:33,070 --> 00:58:34,240
Half those guys on varsity
校队有一半人

941
00:58:34,260 --> 00:58:35,530
competed at Poughkeepsie last year.
去年在波基普西参加过比赛

942
00:58:35,690 --> 00:58:37,050
- And they lost. - They're better this year.
- 他们输了 - 他们今年更好

943
00:58:37,070 --> 00:58:38,370
If you didn't know their ages,
如果不知道他们的年龄

944
00:58:38,490 --> 00:58:40,160
you didn't know how long they've been rowing,
不知道他们划了多久

945
00:58:40,530 --> 00:58:42,030
you're looking at both boats for the first time...
假设你第一次看到这两艘艇...

946
00:58:42,110 --> 00:58:44,210
A time trial in the backyard does not count.
后院的计时赛不算

947
00:58:44,310 --> 00:58:45,700
That is not the same thing as a race.
这和正规赛场是两码事

948
00:58:45,780 --> 00:58:47,120
Look at the competition times.
看看比赛时间

949
00:58:47,140 --> 00:58:48,640
It's not that easy.
没那么容易

950
00:58:49,240 --> 00:58:50,610
Come on, you know that.
拜托, 你知道的

951
00:58:50,660 --> 00:58:51,620
Yes. Yes.
是的, 是的

952
00:58:52,890 --> 00:58:53,970
Yes, I know.
是的, 我知道

953
00:58:54,010 --> 00:58:55,840
You're acting like the varsity boat is scrappin'.
你表现得就像校队是群废物一样

954
00:58:55,890 --> 00:58:58,130
You know that boat hasn't lost a race either.
要知道, 那艘艇也没有输过比赛

955
00:58:58,340 --> 00:58:59,640
And it wasn't that long ago
就在不久前

956
00:58:59,680 --> 00:59:01,320
you were just hopin' the JV boat
你还在期待初级队

957
00:59:01,340 --> 00:59:03,180
was gonna make it to the finish line without sinking.
能在不沉没的情况下坚持到终点

958
00:59:03,210 --> 00:59:04,710
Now, Al,
现在, 艾尔

959
00:59:04,740 --> 00:59:06,530
now you're talkin' about putting all our chips on 'em.
现在你却说要把我们所有的筹码都押在他们身上

960
00:59:06,570 --> 00:59:08,500
Do you think varsity could medal in Berlin?
你认为校队能在柏林拿奖吗？

961
00:59:08,530 --> 00:59:09,990
We're not talkin' about a medal.
我们不是在谈论奖牌

962
00:59:10,010 --> 00:59:11,450
We're talkin' about a shot at gettin' there.
我们说的是去那里的机会

963
00:59:11,490 --> 00:59:13,230
If they got there?
就算他们到了那？

964
00:59:15,840 --> 00:59:17,170
I don't know.
我不知道

965
00:59:27,820 --> 00:59:29,690
We need a win this year, Al.
我们今年需要一场胜利, 艾尔

966
00:59:30,810 --> 00:59:33,380
The people who pay us, they need a win.
给我们付钱的人 他们需要一场胜利

967
00:59:33,980 --> 00:59:36,320
You send a boat full of kids down there
你派一艇孩子过去

968
00:59:36,340 --> 00:59:37,750
and they trip up,
他们就会被绊倒

969
00:59:38,070 --> 00:59:39,740
you're sticking your neck way out there.
你就等着

970
00:59:39,820 --> 00:59:42,690
Makes it a real easy target. And mine, too.
引颈就戮吧 我也是

971
00:59:43,500 --> 00:59:44,970
I need this job.
我需要这份工作

972
01:00:01,450 --> 01:00:02,910
What do you think, George?
你怎么看, 乔治？

973
01:00:03,810 --> 01:00:04,840
Hmm.
嗯

974
01:00:09,830 --> 01:00:11,390
When you were in a boat,
你在艇上那会

975
01:00:11,790 --> 01:00:15,120
you rowed like no one else that's ever come through here.
你的划艇技术这里无人能及

976
01:00:15,140 --> 01:00:16,580
I remember watching you,
我记得我看着你

977
01:00:16,660 --> 01:00:18,860
wondering how fast one of my shells could go
真想知道我的船到底能跑多快

978
01:00:18,890 --> 01:00:20,920
if there were eight just like you in it.
如果里面有八个和你一样的人

979
01:00:22,340 --> 01:00:24,080
That bunch of kids
那群孩子

980
01:00:25,130 --> 01:00:27,730
might be as close to that as I'll ever get.
可能是最接近我这想法的了

981
01:00:30,030 --> 01:00:33,330
And if I send them out there and they aren't ready?
如果我把他们派出去, 他们还没准备好呢？

982
01:00:33,360 --> 01:00:34,990
Then it's like Tom said.
那就像汤姆说的那样

983
01:00:35,370 --> 01:00:37,540
The axe will likely fall,
斧头很可能会落下

984
01:00:37,770 --> 01:00:39,030
and fall hard.
砍得脖子疼

985
01:00:39,550 --> 01:00:41,510
Now you're starting to sound like my wife.
现在你的口气开始像我妻子了

986
01:00:41,970 --> 01:00:44,310
Well, Hazel's a smart woman.
海泽尔是个聪明的女人

987
01:00:44,340 --> 01:00:46,440
I'll take that as a compliment.
我就当你在夸我

988
01:00:54,510 --> 01:00:56,480
Good morning, everybody.
大家早上好

989
01:00:57,450 --> 01:00:58,660
Thank you.
谢谢

990
01:01:00,220 --> 01:01:03,060
Now, as we all know, uh, the Poughkeepsie Regatta
众所周知, 波基普西帆艇赛

991
01:01:03,080 --> 01:01:05,860
is always the most important race of the season.
一直是本赛季最重要的比赛

992
01:01:08,800 --> 01:01:11,110
This year, there's even more riding on it,
今年, 它的意义更加重大

993
01:01:11,140 --> 01:01:14,650
because the winner will qualify for an Olympic spot.
因为获胜者将获得奥运会的参赛资格

994
01:01:14,680 --> 01:01:16,710
Yes!
好

995
01:01:20,840 --> 01:01:23,910
It's also a race that the University of Washington
它也是华盛顿大学已近二十年

996
01:01:24,610 --> 01:01:27,480
has not won in almost two decades,
未尝胜绩的一个赛事

997
01:01:27,550 --> 01:01:30,110
but... but...
但是...

998
01:01:31,740 --> 01:01:34,580
we have a boat this year
我们今年有一艘艇

999
01:01:34,720 --> 01:01:36,860
that I believe could change all that.
我相信他们可以改变这一切

1000
01:01:38,850 --> 01:01:41,920
A boat that could not only win at Poughkeepsie,
这艘艇不仅能在波基普西夺冠

1001
01:01:42,600 --> 01:01:43,730
but
而且

1002
01:01:44,090 --> 01:01:46,260
is strong enough to have a real shot in Berlin.
有足够的实力在柏林一展身手

1003
01:02:03,270 --> 01:02:04,470
And, uh...
还有...

1004
01:02:06,890 --> 01:02:08,990
that boat is our junior boat.
那艘艇就是我们的初级艇

1005
01:02:12,170 --> 01:02:13,660
Yeah, you heard me.
是的, 你们都听到了

1006
01:02:15,650 --> 01:02:17,880
Listen, I understand that that's unorthodox.
听着, 我知道这不合常理

1007
01:02:17,930 --> 01:02:20,270
- Unorthodox? It's insane. - I'm doing everything I can...
- 不合常理？简直是疯了 - 我正在尽我所能...

1008
01:02:20,300 --> 01:02:21,460
You can't do that.
你不能这么做

1009
01:02:21,490 --> 01:02:22,870
in the best interests of our team
我们团队和华盛顿大学的

1010
01:02:22,900 --> 01:02:24,370
and the University of Washington.
最佳利益

1011
01:02:24,400 --> 01:02:26,000
Thank you.
谢谢

1012
01:02:32,590 --> 01:02:33,900
This is bullshit!
这简直是胡扯！

1013
01:02:37,620 --> 01:02:39,050
Have you lost your mind?
你疯了吗？

1014
01:02:39,210 --> 01:02:40,360
What about those boys who spent
那些花了四年时间

1015
01:02:40,390 --> 01:02:41,890
the last four years working for this?
在这上面的孩子怎么办？

1016
01:02:41,990 --> 01:02:43,430
My job is to put the best boat in the water, Ben.
我的工作就是派最好的艇去参赛, 本

1017
01:02:43,450 --> 01:02:45,320
Your job? I pay for your job.
你的工作？我付的钱

1018
01:02:45,760 --> 01:02:46,870
Without the boosters, where do you think
没有我支持, 你认为

1019
01:02:46,890 --> 01:02:48,160
the money for your boats comes from, huh?
你们买艇的钱是从哪里来的？

1020
01:02:48,180 --> 01:02:49,320
For your goddamn salary?
你那该死的薪水哪里来

1021
01:02:49,340 --> 01:02:50,630
How about you let me do my job?
让我做我的工作怎么样？

1022
01:02:50,660 --> 01:02:51,860
Let's just settle down
让我们安定下来

1023
01:02:51,990 --> 01:02:53,760
and talk about this calmly. Come on.
冷静地谈谈 来吧

1024
01:02:53,780 --> 01:02:55,240
There's nothin' to talk about, Jay.
没什么好谈的 杰伊

1025
01:02:55,300 --> 01:02:56,770
My team, my decision.
我的团队, 我做主

1026
01:02:57,010 --> 01:02:58,640
Then it's not your team anymore.
那就不再是你的团队了

1027
01:02:58,830 --> 01:03:00,330
I'll make sure your ass is fired
我会让你屁股挪窝

1028
01:03:00,360 --> 01:03:01,570
before the train leaves for Poughkeepsie.
在火车开往波基普西之前

1029
01:03:01,610 --> 01:03:03,050
- Ben, we're not gonna get... - All right.
- 本, 我们不会搞到... - 好吧

1030
01:03:03,100 --> 01:03:04,670
Bolles is just as capable as you.
博勒斯和你一样能干

1031
01:03:04,800 --> 01:03:05,730
Better even.
甚至更好

1032
01:03:05,800 --> 01:03:07,370
I'd do the same as Al.
我会和艾尔一样选择

1033
01:03:16,090 --> 01:03:17,830
I hope you know what you're doing.
我希望你知道自己在做什么

1034
01:03:19,680 --> 01:03:20,950
Ben!
本

1035
01:03:26,950 --> 01:03:28,220
Do I?
我知道吗？

1036
01:03:30,040 --> 01:03:31,310
Sure you do.
你当然知道

1037
01:03:33,950 --> 01:03:35,560
I can't believe you're going to the Olympics.
真不敢相信你要去参加奥运会

1038
01:03:35,750 --> 01:03:37,180
We gotta beat those other schools first,
我们得先打败其他学校

1039
01:03:37,200 --> 01:03:39,860
but Coach says we have as good a shot as anybody.
但教练说, 我们的机会和其他队一样多

1040
01:03:40,970 --> 01:03:43,350
You can't flirt with any of those New York girls.
你不准和那些纽约女孩调情

1041
01:03:56,500 --> 01:03:57,760
What's wrong?
怎么了？

1042
01:03:59,270 --> 01:04:00,570
Be back in a second.
马上回来

1043
01:04:05,590 --> 01:04:06,830
Joe?
乔？

1044
01:04:39,330 --> 01:04:41,340
Saw your picture in the paper.
在报纸上看到你的照片了

1045
01:04:42,090 --> 01:04:43,900
Harry Junior clipped it out.
小哈利把它剪了下来

1046
01:04:46,160 --> 01:04:47,920
When did you get back from California?
你们什么时候从加州回来的？

1047
01:04:47,950 --> 01:04:49,350
Couple of years.
好几年了

1048
01:04:49,860 --> 01:04:52,260
You know, things weren't much better down there.
那里的情况也没好到哪里去

1049
01:04:53,750 --> 01:04:55,780
So, you've been here all that time?
这么说, 你一直都在这里？

1050
01:04:55,880 --> 01:04:57,070
Down the road a bit.
就在前面一点点远

1051
01:04:57,220 --> 01:04:58,590
Were you ever gonna tell me?
你打算告诉我吗？

1052
01:04:58,810 --> 01:05:00,320
You're doin' all right.
你做得很好

1053
01:05:00,580 --> 01:05:01,780
I was 14 when you left.
你离开的时候, 我才 14 岁

1054
01:05:01,800 --> 01:05:04,040
I went to war when I was that age.
我在那个年纪就上战场了

1055
01:05:09,760 --> 01:05:11,320
So, what do you wanna do, Joe?
那么, 你在想什么, 乔？

1056
01:05:12,490 --> 01:05:13,720
Huh?
啊？

1057
01:05:14,010 --> 01:05:15,040
Move home?
想搬回家吗？

1058
01:05:15,290 --> 01:05:16,620
I mean, I could use the help.
我是说, 我需要人帮忙

1059
01:05:16,760 --> 01:05:18,260
Tell you what, I'll pay you a dollar a day
这样吧, 我每天付你一美元

1060
01:05:18,360 --> 01:05:20,390
if you still remember how to cut a tree.
如果你还记得如何砍树的话

1061
01:05:24,300 --> 01:05:27,100
Or maybe you'd rather just keep rowing your boat.
或者, 你宁愿继续划你的艇

1062
01:05:30,200 --> 01:05:31,970
You don't owe me a thing, Joe.
你不欠我什么 乔

1063
01:05:33,480 --> 01:05:34,570
I don't owe you.
我也不欠你的

1064
01:05:35,410 --> 01:05:37,020
You're doing just fine.
你做得很好

1065
01:05:39,880 --> 01:05:41,610
I'll pass on regards.
我会转达问候的

1066
01:05:56,300 --> 01:05:57,500
I'm sorry.
对不起

1067
01:05:59,770 --> 01:06:01,370
Works out for the best.
这结果是最好的

1068
01:06:05,220 --> 01:06:07,580
Yeah, but that doesn't make it okay.
是的, 但这并不意味着就没事了

1069
01:06:08,800 --> 01:06:10,140
Maybe.
也许吧

1070
01:06:17,540 --> 01:06:19,040
I gotta go.
我得走了

1071
01:07:06,240 --> 01:07:07,640
You should come get some sleep
你应该来睡一觉

1072
01:07:07,670 --> 01:07:09,770
before the sun rises over that.
在太阳升起之前

1073
01:07:10,400 --> 01:07:12,110
I'll be in there soon.
我很快就过去

1074
01:07:17,350 --> 01:07:19,880
I sure love that view.
我真喜欢这样的景色

1075
01:07:22,950 --> 01:07:24,160
I know.
我知道

1076
01:07:25,560 --> 01:07:29,330
I just wish I could enjoy it the way I used to.
我只是希望我能像以前那样享受它

1077
01:07:30,700 --> 01:07:31,760
Why don't you
为什么不能

1078
01:07:32,400 --> 01:07:35,300
come see if there's another view you can enjoy?
要来看看有没有其他风景可以欣赏吗？

1079
01:07:45,580 --> 01:07:46,640
Okay.
好吧

1080
01:08:30,350 --> 01:08:31,520
Thank you.
谢谢

1081
01:08:32,740 --> 01:08:35,130
We're gonna be the fastest crew the world has ever seen.
我们会成为世界上最快的艇员

1082
01:08:35,730 --> 01:08:37,070
Bring home the championship, Al!
把冠军带回家, 艾尔

1083
01:08:37,160 --> 01:08:39,200
- And a gold medal! - We'll try.
- 还有一枚金牌 - 我们会努力的

1084
01:08:40,330 --> 01:08:41,330
Oh, boy.
哦, 天哪

1085
01:08:41,840 --> 01:08:44,280
We might wanna try and win this thing, huh?
我们可能想赢得比赛, 对吧？

1086
01:08:44,940 --> 01:08:46,240
No pressure.
没有压力

1087
01:08:47,550 --> 01:08:49,240
- Good luck! - Bring it home, boys!
- 祝你们好运 - 把奖牌带回家, 孩子们

1088
01:08:49,510 --> 01:08:51,440
I'll be listening on the radio.
我会通过收音机收听

1089
01:08:52,680 --> 01:08:54,740
Say hello if they interview you.
如果他们采访你, 跟我问个好

1090
01:08:56,720 --> 01:08:58,250
This might be a good time to tell you
现在也许是个好机会

1091
01:08:58,280 --> 01:08:59,790
that I'm in love with you, Joe.
告诉你我爱上你了 乔

1092
01:09:01,040 --> 01:09:03,870
All right. I gotta go.
好, 我得走了

1093
01:09:13,600 --> 01:09:15,770
Hey! Hey!
嘿！

1094
01:09:16,760 --> 01:09:18,340
Yeah, she looked at me.
是的, 她看着我

1095
01:09:57,440 --> 01:09:58,640
Rantz!
兰茨

1096
01:10:32,380 --> 01:10:33,950
I'm busted. Someone give me a penny.
我破产了 谁给我一便士

1097
01:10:34,080 --> 01:10:35,080
Lucky, I'll let you watch.
幸运, 我会让你看看的

1098
01:10:35,210 --> 01:10:36,300
Hey, Joe, give me your jacket.
嘿, 乔, 把你的夹克给我

1099
01:10:36,450 --> 01:10:37,850
That'll get me halfway to ante.
这样我有一半押注的钱了

1100
01:10:38,040 --> 01:10:39,350
Joe, stick around.
乔, 别走

1101
01:10:39,480 --> 01:10:41,220
Hey, don't run away, Hobo Joe.
嘿, 别走啊, 流浪汉乔

1102
01:10:44,300 --> 01:10:45,570
He's playin'.
他开玩笑的

1103
01:10:46,390 --> 01:10:48,120
He's playin'. He's playin'.
他开玩笑的 他开玩笑的

1104
01:10:48,250 --> 01:10:49,480
He's playin'.
他开玩笑的

1105
01:10:54,160 --> 01:10:56,430
- Jesus, Chuck. - Was just jokin'.
- 天啊, 查克 - 开个玩笑而已

1106
01:10:57,460 --> 01:10:59,260
Yeah, well, your jokes are lousy.
好吧, 你的笑话太烂了

1107
01:11:38,600 --> 01:11:40,200
I didn't mean anything by it.
我没有别的意思

1108
01:11:42,250 --> 01:11:45,450
Truth is, my old man went bust years ago, so...
事实是, 我老爸几年前就破产了, 所以...

1109
01:11:46,060 --> 01:11:48,930
Any new clothes I wear, I swipe from Woolworth's.
我穿的新衣服, 都是从伍尔沃斯超市顺来的

1110
01:11:51,190 --> 01:11:52,450
Doesn't matter.
无所谓

1111
01:11:54,370 --> 01:11:56,140
Just sayin' we're not different.
我只是说, 我们并没有什么不同

1112
01:11:56,630 --> 01:11:57,830
You and me.
你和我

1113
01:11:59,920 --> 01:12:01,720
Except you're not a thief.
只不过你不是小偷

1114
01:12:18,220 --> 01:12:20,020
One! Way-nuff!
一 停桨

1115
01:12:20,320 --> 01:12:21,520
Drop it.
放下

1116
01:12:22,350 --> 01:12:24,950
Again! Need to get sharper.
再来一次！节奏再快一点

1117
01:12:25,100 --> 01:12:26,130
Come on.
来吧

1118
01:12:26,260 --> 01:12:28,170
You guys are out of sync. Find Hume.
你们不同步 跟着休姆

1119
01:12:28,300 --> 01:12:29,440
Take it off Hume.
跟着休姆的节奏

1120
01:12:29,570 --> 01:12:31,170
Look like a team, fellas.
像个团队, 伙计们

1121
01:12:31,330 --> 01:12:32,530
As one.
同步

1122
01:12:32,550 --> 01:12:33,710
You're out of sync.
你们不同步

1123
01:12:33,830 --> 01:12:36,080
Okay, no, no. Way-nuff.
好吧 不 停桨

1124
01:12:37,230 --> 01:12:39,190
Where are we off? Hey, Joe, you with us?
我们要去哪里？嘿, 乔, 你和我们在一起吗？

1125
01:12:39,270 --> 01:12:40,910
- Me? - Yeah, lock in on Don.
- 我 - 对 锁定唐的节奏

1126
01:12:40,930 --> 01:12:42,650
What are you talkin' about? I'm not the problem.
你在说什么？我不是问题所在

1127
01:12:44,220 --> 01:12:45,390
Go again.
再来一次

1128
01:12:46,030 --> 01:12:47,000
Come on.
来吧

1129
01:12:47,050 --> 01:12:48,410
In and through.
破 划

1130
01:12:48,610 --> 01:12:49,840
In and through.
破 划

1131
01:12:50,200 --> 01:12:52,740
All right, give me three more. Three,
好吧, 再来三桨 三

1132
01:12:53,140 --> 01:12:54,140
two,
二

1133
01:12:55,070 --> 01:12:56,930
one. Way-nuff!
一 停桨

1134
01:12:57,930 --> 01:12:59,360
That'd get us a solid sixth.
这样我们肯定能拿到第六名

1135
01:12:59,390 --> 01:13:01,730
It's new water, they're still getting comfortable.
这是新水域, 他们还没适应

1136
01:13:02,330 --> 01:13:03,460
First times were faster.
第一轮还比较快

1137
01:13:03,490 --> 01:13:04,600
They're getting less comfortable.
他们越来越不协调了

1138
01:13:04,630 --> 01:13:05,770
What is the matter?
怎么回事？

1139
01:13:05,860 --> 01:13:07,690
Not in tune yet. I'll get 'em there, Coach.
还没协调好 我会带好他们的 教练

1140
01:13:07,750 --> 01:13:09,690
Let's do it before the race, Bobby.
让我们在赛前先协调好吧 鲍比

1141
01:13:11,080 --> 01:13:11,980
Go again.
再来一次

1142
01:13:12,000 --> 01:13:13,760
All right, fellas. Port side, back it down.
好了 伙计们 左舷 退后

1143
01:13:13,870 --> 01:13:16,170
Starboard, tap on. Ready?
右舷 打开 准备好了吗？

1144
01:13:17,520 --> 01:13:19,010
<i>Probably nervous.</i>
<i>可能是紧张</i>

1145
01:13:19,840 --> 01:13:21,400
<i>They're just kids, Al.</i>
<i>他们只是孩子, 艾尔</i>

1146
01:13:22,680 --> 01:13:24,420
<i>That's why everybody told me
这就是为什么大家都告诉我</i>

1147
01:13:24,440 --> 01:13:26,070
<i>I was wrong for bringin' them.</i>
<i>我不该带他们来</i>

1148
01:13:28,210 --> 01:13:30,570
I just can't afford for them to be kids.
我没有本钱再让他们孩子气下去了

1149
01:13:32,020 --> 01:13:33,290
Not anymore.
现在不一样了

1150
01:14:11,920 --> 01:14:13,840
- It looks like they... - I know what's wrong.
- 看起来他们... - 我知道问题在哪了

1151
01:14:14,150 --> 01:14:15,410
Bring it in.
带进来

1152
01:14:16,150 --> 01:14:18,160
You have 500 perfect meters.
你们完美地划了五百米

1153
01:14:18,840 --> 01:14:20,440
And then another five, where it looks like
然后另外五百米, 看起来就像

1154
01:14:20,470 --> 01:14:21,730
you're rowing eight different boats.
你们在划八条不同的艇

1155
01:14:21,750 --> 01:14:23,120
The timing's just a little off.
时间就是有点对不上

1156
01:14:23,430 --> 01:14:25,230
Joe, where is your head at, son?
乔, 你的心思在哪里呢, 孩子？

1157
01:14:26,250 --> 01:14:27,680
- It's in the boat. - No, it's not.
- 在艇上 - 不, 不在

1158
01:14:27,710 --> 01:14:29,040
You're setting your own pace.
你在跟着自己的节奏走

1159
01:14:29,290 --> 01:14:30,550
Your catch is higher than the rest.
你的入水高于其他人

1160
01:14:30,580 --> 01:14:32,150
- I'm trying to... - Don't interrupt me.
- 我想...- 别打断我

1161
01:14:32,180 --> 01:14:33,650
You're rowing like you're in a single.
你就像在单人划艇一样

1162
01:14:33,680 --> 01:14:35,560
We've been doing this too goddamn long to forget
我们已经训练太久了, 不可能忘记

1163
01:14:35,590 --> 01:14:37,490
you're in an eight-man shell.
你是在一个八人艇上

1164
01:14:37,860 --> 01:14:39,220
Now, do you wanna be in the boat
现在, 你想在艇上吗？

1165
01:14:39,250 --> 01:14:41,400
or am I'm gonna put someone else in your seat?
还是我让别人来坐你的位子？

1166
01:14:43,180 --> 01:14:44,450
I don't care.
我不在乎

1167
01:14:50,480 --> 01:14:51,540
Coy!
科伊

1168
01:14:52,160 --> 01:14:53,560
You're in Rantz's seat.
你坐在兰茨的位置上

1169
01:14:54,870 --> 01:14:57,350
Get out. You don't care? Get out.
滚出去 你不在乎？滚出去

1170
01:15:00,920 --> 01:15:02,620
Coy, come on, let's go.
科伊, 来吧, 我们走

1171
01:15:04,980 --> 01:15:06,950
Looks like you're racin' tomorrow.
看来你明天要参加比赛了

1172
01:15:16,280 --> 01:15:19,350
Now, maybe we can row as a team.
现在, 也许我们可以像一个团队一样划了

1173
01:15:25,700 --> 01:15:27,500
And just go talk to Coach, tell him you want back in.
去和教练谈谈 告诉他你想回去

1174
01:15:27,520 --> 01:15:29,280
I'm not beggin' him to give my place back.
我不会求他把我的位置还给我的

1175
01:15:29,460 --> 01:15:30,850
- I'm done with that. - Where you gonna go?
- 我受够了 - 你要去哪儿？

1176
01:15:30,880 --> 01:15:32,150
Ain't like you got money enough for a train ticket.
你的钱又不够买张火车票

1177
01:15:32,180 --> 01:15:33,510
I'll figure somethin' out. I always have.
我会想办法的 我一向如此

1178
01:15:33,530 --> 01:15:35,340
Are you gonna live in a car in Poughkeepsie?
你要在波基普西找个车住进去吗？

1179
01:15:37,240 --> 01:15:39,200
Hello, Roger. Hello, Joe.
你好 罗杰 你好 乔

1180
01:15:40,140 --> 01:15:42,780
I need to put another coat on the <i>Husky Clipper.</i>
我需要在 "赫斯基快艇" 上再涂一层漆

1181
01:15:43,160 --> 01:15:44,560
I could use a hand.
需要人帮忙

1182
01:16:00,080 --> 01:16:03,760
My grandfather would let me help oil the shells he built.
我爷爷会让我帮他造的船上油

1183
01:16:04,110 --> 01:16:06,590
Most hate it because of the smell.
大多数人讨厌它是因为有味道

1184
01:16:06,980 --> 01:16:10,820
I catch the scent of whale oil and immediately hear his voice
我一闻到鲸油的味道, 立刻就听到了他的声音

1185
01:16:10,920 --> 01:16:12,330
telling me to, "Keep putting it on"
告诉我 "继续涂"

1186
01:16:12,410 --> 01:16:14,760
"until you can see your freckles in the reflection."
"直到你能从反光中看到你脸上的雀斑"

1187
01:16:15,830 --> 01:16:18,070
That's how I'd know it was good and slick.
这样我才知道它又好又滑

1188
01:16:19,030 --> 01:16:22,630
So it would cut through the water like a knife blade.
这样, 它就能像刀刃一样划过水面

1189
01:16:23,940 --> 01:16:25,870
How it didn't matter how fast someone rowed
划得再快也没用

1190
01:16:25,900 --> 01:16:28,260
if the water didn't flow across the hull
如果水不是以完全正确的方式

1191
01:16:29,310 --> 01:16:31,100
in the exact right way.
流过船体

1192
01:16:32,710 --> 01:16:35,320
If the weight wasn't balanced just right.
如果重量没有恰到好处地平衡

1193
01:16:35,970 --> 01:16:38,300
Every piece working with the other.
每一部分都要相互配合

1194
01:16:42,570 --> 01:16:44,390
It's the same with the crew.
艇员也是一样

1195
01:16:45,490 --> 01:16:48,520
So much that there's really no difference between the two.
以至于两者之间真的没有什么区别

1196
01:16:50,140 --> 01:16:54,080
They're connected by all the hours spent together.
他们因一起度过的所有时光而团结在一起

1197
01:16:54,960 --> 01:16:56,510
Sweat and pain
汗水和痛苦

1198
01:16:57,050 --> 01:17:00,320
bleeds into the grain as they become one magical thing
洇湿了艇身的纹理, 它们变成了在水面上穿梭的

1199
01:17:00,340 --> 01:17:01,540
that moves across the water
一个神奇的东西

1200
01:17:01,570 --> 01:17:03,840
like it was born to be nowhere else.
就像天生就不属于任何地方一样

1201
01:17:07,100 --> 01:17:10,370
I've built a lot of good boats, but the best ones,
我造过很多好船，但最好的艇

1202
01:17:10,630 --> 01:17:14,610
the boats where every part fits exactly as it should,
每一个部件都完全吻合的艇

1203
01:17:14,630 --> 01:17:18,340
where every man trusts the one behind him,
每一个人都信任他身后的人的艇

1204
01:17:18,360 --> 01:17:20,840
they are the boats people remember forever.
才是人们永远铭记的艇

1205
01:17:23,620 --> 01:17:25,400
That's what this boat could be.
这就是这艘艇可能成为的样子

1206
01:17:25,820 --> 01:17:27,280
Be a shame for anyone to miss
看看这艘所有部件都完美配合的艇能跑多快

1207
01:17:27,300 --> 01:17:29,930
seeing how fast it could go with all the right pieces.
如果有人错过了 那就太可惜了

1208
01:17:35,890 --> 01:17:39,060
Joe, your dad gave up on you. He quit on you.
乔 你爸爸放弃了你 他放弃了你

1209
01:17:39,450 --> 01:17:41,120
All you know is quitting.
你就只会放弃

1210
01:17:45,480 --> 01:17:47,860
But it seems to me you're not him.
但在我看来, 你不是他

1211
01:17:52,780 --> 01:17:54,120
Or are you?
或者你是？

1212
01:18:26,280 --> 01:18:28,250
- Yes. - Yes, it's very nice.
- 是的 - 是的, 非常好

1213
01:18:31,570 --> 01:18:33,830
If I can get you two to just stand together.
如果你们两个能站在一起的话

1214
01:18:33,950 --> 01:18:36,510
Just for one. And perfect.
再来一张 完美

1215
01:19:00,060 --> 01:19:02,490
I'll, uh, see you over there.
我们那边见

1216
01:19:12,420 --> 01:19:14,290
What can I do for you, Joe?
我能为你做什么, 乔？

1217
01:19:16,750 --> 01:19:18,220
I want my seat back.
我想要回我的位置

1218
01:19:20,250 --> 01:19:21,470
Why?
为什么？

1219
01:19:22,580 --> 01:19:24,410
All that time I spent in it,
我在里面度过的那些时光

1220
01:19:24,570 --> 01:19:26,610
the work we all did together...
我们一起付出的努力

1221
01:19:29,070 --> 01:19:30,450
That boat...
那艘艇...

1222
01:19:33,670 --> 01:19:35,060
it's all I got.
是我的全部

1223
01:19:35,530 --> 01:19:37,030
The boys and...
伙计们和...

1224
01:19:40,850 --> 01:19:42,450
It's all I got.
我只有这些了

1225
01:19:42,530 --> 01:19:43,960
I can't lose that.
我不能失去

1226
01:19:51,560 --> 01:19:53,880
You know, one of the first things I said to you boys was
我对你们说的第一件事就是

1227
01:19:53,900 --> 01:19:57,180
there's no shame if your body can't hold up to this.
如果你的身体承受不了, 这并不丢人

1228
01:19:58,620 --> 01:20:00,520
The same goes for the mind.
精神也是一样

1229
01:20:01,940 --> 01:20:04,440
Listen, I know it isn't easy to trust every other person
听着, 我知道要信任那条艇上的每一个人

1230
01:20:04,580 --> 01:20:07,420
on that boat as much as you trust yourself.
就像信任自己一样 并不容易

1231
01:20:07,470 --> 01:20:08,760
But it's not about you.
但这与你无关

1232
01:20:10,250 --> 01:20:12,770
As good as you are, it's not about you, Joe,
虽然你很优秀 但这不是你一个人的事情 乔

1233
01:20:12,800 --> 01:20:14,570
or me, or anybody else.
或者我, 或其他任何一个人

1234
01:20:14,710 --> 01:20:16,180
It's about the boat.
这是关于艇的

1235
01:20:17,860 --> 01:20:19,030
Yes, sir.
是的, 先生

1236
01:20:19,710 --> 01:20:21,130
It's where I wanna be.
这是我想去的地方

1237
01:20:27,000 --> 01:20:28,430
Okay.
好的

1238
01:20:30,420 --> 01:20:32,200
Well, you better get dressed.
你最好穿上队服

1239
01:20:34,100 --> 01:20:35,300
Thank you.
谢谢

1240
01:20:36,570 --> 01:20:38,270
Really, thank you.
真的, 谢谢你

1241
01:20:46,340 --> 01:20:47,670
<i>Today's regatta</i>
<i>今天的帆艇赛</i>

1242
01:20:47,770 --> 01:20:49,700
<i>is as much a social experiment as it is a race.</i>
<i>它既是一场比赛, 也是一场社会实验</i>

1243
01:20:50,020 --> 01:20:51,360
<i>A clash of character.</i>
<i>一场富有精英</i>

1244
01:20:51,380 --> 01:20:53,790
<i>Of old money versus no money at all.</i>
<i>和平头百姓的角色冲突</i>

1245
01:20:53,930 --> 01:20:57,410
Six boats of want-to's against one filled with have-to's.
六艘生活之艇对上一艘生存之艇

1246
01:20:57,540 --> 01:20:59,900
<i>These nine working-class boys arrived from the American West</i>
<i>这九个工人阶级男孩从美国西部来到这里</i>

1247
01:21:00,030 --> 01:21:01,970
<i>on the shoulders of a country that sees itself</i>
<i>肩负着一个国家的重任 这个国家从他们</i>

1248
01:21:02,110 --> 01:21:03,670
<i>in their determined young faces.</i>
<i>坚定的年轻面孔中看到了自己</i>

1249
01:21:03,810 --> 01:21:05,610
<i>Sees their struggles, their grit, their spirit.</i>
<i>看到他们的奋斗 勇气和精神</i>

1250
01:21:05,740 --> 01:21:08,230
<i>And they've claimed the</i> Husky Clipper <i>as their own.</i>
<i>他们将 </i>"赫斯基快艇号" <i>视作自身</i>

1251
01:21:08,380 --> 01:21:09,800
<i>Because it's a boat full of underdogs</i>
<i>因为艇上都是弱者</i>

1252
01:21:09,830 --> 01:21:11,530
<i>representing an underdog nation.</i>
<i>代表一个弱势民族</i>

1253
01:21:11,820 --> 01:21:13,520
<i>A nation of people who have been beaten down</i>
<i>一个被打倒</i>

1254
01:21:13,610 --> 01:21:15,040
<i>but refuse to go away.</i>
<i>但拒绝离开的民族</i>

1255
01:21:15,340 --> 01:21:17,440
<i>Refuse to stop working hard, 'cause that's all they know.</i>
<i>拒绝停止努力工作, 因为他们只知道努力工作</i>

1256
01:21:17,600 --> 01:21:18,840
<i>All they have ever done.</i>
<i>只会努力工作</i>

1257
01:21:19,650 --> 01:21:22,750
<i>So, find your place, by the river or the radio.</i>
<i>所以, 找好你的位置, 在河边或收音机旁</i>

1258
01:21:23,370 --> 01:21:25,090
<i>And cheer for guts and heart and brawn</i>
<i>今天，我们要为勇气、心智和体力喝彩</i>

1259
01:21:25,160 --> 01:21:28,760
<i>to beat privilege and prestige to the finish line today.</i>
<i>战胜特权和名望, 冲向终点</i>

1260
01:21:29,410 --> 01:21:31,370
<i>Cheer for the boys from Washington.
为来自华盛顿的小伙子们欢呼</i>

1261
01:21:34,150 --> 01:21:36,720
Listen up. We're in lane seven.
听好了 我们在第七道

1262
01:21:37,140 --> 01:21:39,490
Navy and Cal are gonna wanna jump to a lead.
