01:28:42,750 --> 01:28:43,960
what was the feeling in the boat
在艇上的感觉如何

1427
01:28:43,980 --> 01:28:45,210
when you were four lengths back?
在你们落后四个艇位的时候？

1428
01:28:45,290 --> 01:28:46,620
Was there any panic?
有没有恐慌？

1429
01:28:49,690 --> 01:28:51,220
Uh, there was no panic.
没有恐慌

1430
01:28:51,270 --> 01:28:52,480
All of us,
我们所有人

1431
01:28:52,500 --> 01:28:54,720
we knew we could make up the ground when we needed to.
我们都知道我们可以在需要的时候到位

1432
01:28:54,880 --> 01:28:56,280
And, if I could,
如果可以的话

1433
01:28:56,450 --> 01:28:58,940
could I say hello to my girl Joyce back home?
我能跟我的乔伊斯打个招呼吗？

1434
01:28:59,100 --> 01:29:01,620
<i>I'll let you wear the gold medal when I get back.</i>
<i>等我回来就让你戴上金牌</i>

1435
01:29:02,390 --> 01:29:03,490
<i>That's right, folks.</i>
<i>没错, 各位</i>

1436
01:29:03,550 --> 01:29:05,210
<i>They'll be bringing the gold medal home</i>
<i>他们将把金牌带回家</i>

1437
01:29:05,240 --> 01:29:06,790
<i>for all of us back in Washington.</i>
<i>为了我们所有华盛顿人</i>

1438
01:29:06,950 --> 01:29:07,870
Oh.
哦

1439
01:29:08,510 --> 01:29:09,920
This is great.
这太棒了

1440
01:29:10,000 --> 01:29:11,900
So, you guys all knew about it when?
你们是什么时候知道的？

1441
01:29:12,020 --> 01:29:13,420
And I'm hearing about it tonight?
我今晚才听到？

1442
01:29:13,470 --> 01:29:14,910
You know what this sounds like to me?
你知道这听起来像什么吗？

1443
01:29:14,930 --> 01:29:16,820
It sounds like you guys are changing the rules
听起来你们好像在改变规则

1444
01:29:16,850 --> 01:29:18,630
because you're trying to steal this from us.
因为你想从我们这里偷走这个

1445
01:29:18,670 --> 01:29:21,780
No one is trying to steal anything, Coach Ulbrickson.
没有人想偷什么 乌尔布里克森教练

1446
01:29:21,800 --> 01:29:22,930
I'm just speaking to you
我只是和你谈谈

1447
01:29:22,960 --> 01:29:25,130
as the U.S. Rowing Olympic Chairman
以美国赛艇奥林匹克主席的身份

1448
01:29:25,160 --> 01:29:26,400
and telling you the facts.
告诉你这个事实

1449
01:29:26,430 --> 01:29:28,240
U.S. Rowing does not have the money
美国赛艇协会没有钱

1450
01:29:28,270 --> 01:29:29,890
to fund your trip to Berlin.
来资助您的柏林之旅

1451
01:29:29,920 --> 01:29:31,250
And how is that even possible?
这怎么可能呢？

1452
01:29:31,270 --> 01:29:32,410
It's not just rowing.
不仅仅是划艇

1453
01:29:32,740 --> 01:29:34,060
Swimming, fencing.
游泳 击剑

1454
01:29:34,080 --> 01:29:35,720
There are many other sports that are dealing with...
还有许多其他体育运动也在面对...

1455
01:29:35,850 --> 01:29:38,750
Exactly how much are we supposed to come up with?
我们到底需要出多少钱？

1456
01:29:40,800 --> 01:29:42,970
- $5,000. - Five?
- 五千美金 - 五千？

1457
01:29:43,140 --> 01:29:44,950
- In a week? - In a week.
- 一周内？ - 一周内

1458
01:29:45,110 --> 01:29:46,740
And what if we can't come up with it?
如果我们拿不出来呢？

1459
01:29:46,760 --> 01:29:48,130
Well, the committee would have to find
委员会不得不去找

1460
01:29:48,190 --> 01:29:50,010
a suitable replacement to compete in Berlin.
合适的接替者去柏林比赛

1461
01:29:50,030 --> 01:29:51,660
Suitable like who, Henry? Like your Penn squad?
谁合适, 亨利？像你的宾大队？

1462
01:29:51,680 --> 01:29:53,950
If necessary, yes.
如果有必要, 可以

1463
01:29:54,330 --> 01:29:56,630
We'd of course give California the first opportunity.
我们当然首先会给加州队一个机会

1464
01:29:57,220 --> 01:29:58,660
Either team is a better option
无论派哪支队去

1465
01:29:58,710 --> 01:30:00,020
than not sending a team at all.
总比不派队好

1466
01:30:00,040 --> 01:30:02,000
This is bullshit, Henry. It's bullshit.
这是废话 亨利 都是胡扯

1467
01:30:02,040 --> 01:30:04,310
You didn't expect us to win, and we won.
你没想到我们会赢, 但我们赢了

1468
01:30:04,580 --> 01:30:06,830
Yeah, you couldn't win on the water. None of you.
是啊, 你们不可能在水上赢我们 你们谁也赢不了

1469
01:30:06,860 --> 01:30:07,970
I don't like this situation.
我不喜欢这种情况

1470
01:30:07,990 --> 01:30:09,630
- Now, you're makin' up the rules. - Bullshit.
- 现在, 你在胡编乱造 - 胡说八道

1471
01:30:09,650 --> 01:30:10,670
I don't like the situation
我也不喜欢这种情况

1472
01:30:10,690 --> 01:30:12,300
- any more than you do. - Yeah, sure you don't.
- 和你一样 - 你当然不喜欢

1473
01:30:12,370 --> 01:30:14,410
- Bullshit. - We'll figure this out.
- 胡说八道 - 我们会解决的

1474
01:30:14,680 --> 01:30:17,390
How are we supposed to come up with $5,000?
我们怎么能拿出 5000 美元呢？

1475
01:30:21,150 --> 01:30:24,490
Our university will reach out to alumni and boosters.
我们大学将与校友和支持者联系

1476
01:30:24,570 --> 01:30:26,830
See if they can scrape anything up.
看看他们能不能支持一点

1477
01:30:27,250 --> 01:30:28,850
And if they can't find enough?
如果他们的资助也不够呢？

1478
01:30:29,460 --> 01:30:31,430
Then it'd be Cal
那就会是加州大学队

1479
01:30:31,540 --> 01:30:33,180
or Penn.
或宾州大学队去了

1480
01:30:33,310 --> 01:30:34,740
We beat those guys.
我们打败了那些家伙

1481
01:30:35,330 --> 01:30:36,630
I know.
我知道

1482
01:30:36,810 --> 01:30:39,200
No way we let those rich pricks go instead of us.
我们绝不能让那些有钱的混蛋代替我们去

1483
01:30:39,900 --> 01:30:41,730
Then we better find some money.
那我们最好找点钱出来

1484
01:30:42,380 --> 01:30:43,490
Yeah.
是啊

1485
01:30:49,290 --> 01:30:50,680
Al, where you goin'?
艾尔, 你去哪儿？

1486
01:31:06,030 --> 01:31:07,370
Help send the Huskies to Berlin.
帮助将哈士奇队送往柏林

1487
01:31:07,430 --> 01:31:08,590
Thank you. You have a nice day.
谢谢 祝您愉快

1488
01:31:08,640 --> 01:31:09,980
- Thank you, sir. - Sure.
- 谢谢 - 好的

1489
01:31:10,120 --> 01:31:11,310
Hey, guys.
嘿, 伙计们

1490
01:31:11,550 --> 01:31:13,070
The Olympic rowing team needs your help to get to Berlin.
奥运赛艇队需要您的帮助才能到达柏林

1491
01:31:13,150 --> 01:31:14,470
We only got a couple days left.
我们只剩下几天时间了

1492
01:31:14,580 --> 01:31:15,980
Fellas, I got a dollar.
伙计们, 我有一块钱

1493
01:31:16,090 --> 01:31:18,690
Spare a couple dollars. Help us beat the Germans.
捐助几块钱 帮助我们打败德国人

1494
01:31:20,920 --> 01:31:22,190
All right.
好的

1495
01:31:23,930 --> 01:31:25,630
Thanks. My name's Roger.
谢谢 我叫罗杰

1496
01:31:25,710 --> 01:31:26,740
Hey, I'm Chuck.
嘿, 我是查克

1497
01:31:26,830 --> 01:31:27,860
Oh, please.
哦, 拜托

1498
01:31:29,200 --> 01:31:30,870
<i>Well, you're running out of days, Coach.</i>
<i>好吧, 你的时间不多了, 教练</i>

1499
01:31:30,960 --> 01:31:33,050
- You have what, four left? - Three.
- 你还缺多少, 四千？- 三千

1500
01:31:33,180 --> 01:31:34,750
And we've only gotten halfway
我们的资金才募集到了

1501
01:31:34,780 --> 01:31:36,920
to what the Olympic Committee says we need.
奥委会说的一半

1502
01:31:37,050 --> 01:31:38,250
<i>So, if you don't raise the money, </i>
<i>所以, 如果你筹不足钱</i>

1503
01:31:38,280 --> 01:31:39,710
<i>you go back to Seattle</i>
<i>你们就得回西雅图去</i>

1504
01:31:39,750 --> 01:31:41,210
<i>while some other team goes to Berlin?</i>
<i>与此同时, 其他队会去柏林？</i>

1505
01:31:41,250 --> 01:31:42,720
<i>Correct. And that goes against</i>
<i>正确 这有悖于</i>

1506
01:31:42,740 --> 01:31:44,420
<i>everything sports should be about.</i>
<i>一切体育精神</i>

1507
01:31:44,580 --> 01:31:47,090
Athletes should be rewarded for performance.
运动员应该因为表现而得到奖励

1508
01:31:47,150 --> 01:31:48,240
No politics,
不搞政治

1509
01:31:48,350 --> 01:31:50,320
<i>no adjusted scoring or selection</i>
<i>不搞加分 或者</i>

1510
01:31:50,460 --> 01:31:52,260
based on wealth and standing.
基于财富和地位来选人

1511
01:31:52,390 --> 01:31:53,960
May the best man win.
让最优秀的人获胜

1512
01:31:54,050 --> 01:31:55,940
<i>That's what they say. That's what it should be.</i>
<i>他们是这么说的 就应该是这样</i>

1513
01:31:56,010 --> 01:31:58,710
These boys, Washington's boys,
这些孩子 华盛顿的孩子

1514
01:31:59,180 --> 01:32:00,650
this country's boys,
这个国家的孩子

1515
01:32:00,670 --> 01:32:01,970
my boys,
我的孩子

1516
01:32:02,060 --> 01:32:05,100
they have proven themselves to be the best.
他们已经证明了自己是最棒的

1517
01:32:08,310 --> 01:32:10,070
Help us send the Huskies to Berlin.
帮助我们将哈士奇队送往柏林

1518
01:32:10,170 --> 01:32:12,180
A reminder, folks, every little bit helps.
提醒各位, 一点一滴都是帮助

1519
01:32:12,310 --> 01:32:13,540
Thank you so much.
非常感谢

1520
01:32:13,710 --> 01:32:14,700
Come on, support our boys.
来吧, 支持我们的孩子

1521
01:32:14,800 --> 01:32:16,070
All right. Thank you so much.
好的 非常感谢

1522
01:32:16,210 --> 01:32:18,310
Thank you so much.
非常感谢

1523
01:32:19,010 --> 01:32:20,910
Thank you so much. Thank you.
非常感谢 谢谢

1524
01:32:39,180 --> 01:32:42,280
We got $92 from Tacoma in honor of Roger Morris.
我们从塔科马募集了 92 美元, 以罗杰·莫里斯之名

1525
01:32:42,300 --> 01:32:44,870
$75 more from Sequim for Joe Rantz.
再加上从塞奎姆给乔·兰茨募集的 75 美元

1526
01:32:45,140 --> 01:32:47,070
$90 from Olympia for Don Hume.
从奥林匹亚给唐·休姆募集的 90 美元

1527
01:32:47,730 --> 01:32:50,670
Every hometown of these boys has given somethin'.
每个孩子的家乡都付出了努力

1528
01:32:51,100 --> 01:32:53,670
Pacific Telegraph just sent $250 this evening.
太平洋电报公司今晚刚寄来 250 美元

1529
01:32:53,700 --> 01:32:54,830
Where does that put us
我们一共筹集了

1530
01:32:54,860 --> 01:32:55,790
with everything else we've got?
多少了现在？

1531
01:32:55,870 --> 01:32:57,440
- Eh, close. - But?
- 嗯, 差不多了 - 但是呢？

1532
01:32:57,580 --> 01:32:59,340
Well, close is just close, Al.
好吧, 接近就是接近, 艾尔

1533
01:32:59,930 --> 01:33:01,520
And we're out of time.
我们没时间了

1534
01:33:04,340 --> 01:33:06,550
Come on.
来吧

1535
01:33:16,250 --> 01:33:19,280
Mrs. Ulbrickson, I'm looking for your husband.
乌尔布里克森太太 我来找你丈夫

1536
01:33:28,620 --> 01:33:30,310
We still got four hours, Ky.
我们还有四个小时呢 凯

1537
01:33:30,440 --> 01:33:32,770
Racing the clock as usual.
像往常一样争分夺秒

1538
01:33:33,380 --> 01:33:34,360
I can't lie to you, Al.
我不能骗你, 艾尔

1539
01:33:34,390 --> 01:33:37,060
My boys would love to go to Berlin.
我的孩子们很想去柏林

1540
01:33:38,200 --> 01:33:39,600
How short are you?
你还缺多少？

1541
01:33:40,800 --> 01:33:42,070
$300.
300美金

1542
01:33:42,490 --> 01:33:43,480
Give or take.
左右

1543
01:33:44,500 --> 01:33:45,490
Hmm.
嗯

1544
01:33:58,360 --> 01:33:59,570
May I?
可以吗？

1545
01:34:15,590 --> 01:34:17,430
This is from the Cal Bears.
这是来自加州熊队的

1546
01:34:19,450 --> 01:34:21,790
An IOU for $300.
一张 300 美元的欠条

1547
01:34:24,040 --> 01:34:25,310
Give or take.
或多或少

1548
01:34:33,040 --> 01:34:34,310
Ky.
凯

1549
01:34:38,680 --> 01:34:41,450
No one deserves to go but your boys.
除了你的孩子们, 没有人有资格去

1550
01:34:44,890 --> 01:34:46,090
Gentlemen.
先生们

1551
01:34:46,930 --> 01:34:48,230
Mrs. Ulbrickson.
乌尔布里克森夫人

1552
01:34:50,040 --> 01:34:53,440
And if there's any extra, you can bring me back a souvenir.
如果钱还有剩的话, 你们可以给我带点纪念品回来

1553
01:35:15,240 --> 01:35:17,070
<i>Aboard the</i> SS Manhattan,
<i>登上</i> SS 曼哈顿号

1554
01:35:17,200 --> 01:35:19,700
<i>a shipload of American athletes sails for Hamburg.</i>
<i>一船美国运动员驶往汉堡</i>

1555
01:35:19,830 --> 01:35:21,840
<i>The Olympic Games, their goal.</i>
<i>奥林匹克运动会, 他们的目标</i>

1556
01:35:22,090 --> 01:35:23,690
<i>Here is Jesse Owens, </i>
<i>这是杰西·欧文斯,</i>

1557
01:35:23,830 --> 01:35:26,570
<i>the one-man track team from the University of Ohio.</i>
<i>俄亥俄大学的一个人组成的田径队</i>

1558
01:35:26,840 --> 01:35:28,600
<i>Some say, "The greatest ever."</i>
<i>有人说是, "有史以来最伟大的"</i>

1559
01:35:28,730 --> 01:35:31,400
<i>More than 300 athletes will march ashore</i>
<i>300 多名运动员将上岸</i>

1560
01:35:31,540 --> 01:35:34,210
<i>on German soil, ready to fight for gold.</i>
<i>在德国的土地上, 准备为金牌而战</i>

1561
01:35:34,780 --> 01:35:37,790
<i>Among the participants are the University of Washington's</i>
<i>参与者包括华盛顿大学的</i>

1562
01:35:37,880 --> 01:35:40,080
<i>junior varsity eight-man rowing crew.</i>
<i>八人赛艇初级队</i>

1563
01:35:40,650 --> 01:35:42,300
<i>The boat is ready to do battle</i>
<i>这艘小艇已经准备好</i>

1564
01:35:42,350 --> 01:35:44,390
<i>with the likes of Italy, Great Britain</i>
<i>与意大利、英国</i>

1565
01:35:44,520 --> 01:35:45,880
<i>and Germany,</i>
<i>和德国等</i>

1566
01:35:45,980 --> 01:35:48,610
<i>all favorites in this most grueling of events.</i>
<i>最受欢迎的队伍一决高下</i>

1567
01:35:49,190 --> 01:35:52,370
<i>In Berlin, the preparations for the Games are complete, </i>
<i>在柏林, 奥运会的筹备工作已经完成</i>

1568
01:35:52,450 --> 01:35:54,760
<i>and the German people are ready to welcome</i>
<i>德国人民已经准备好欢迎</i>

1569
01:35:54,830 --> 01:35:57,300
<i>athletes from 52 countries.</i>
<i>来自 52 个国家的运动员</i>

1570
01:35:57,740 --> 01:35:59,430
<i>German Chancellor Adolf Hitler</i>
<i>德国总理阿道夫·希特勒</i>

1571
01:35:59,530 --> 01:36:01,780
<i>has promised a spectacle like no other, </i>
<i>曾承诺要举办一场无与伦比的盛会,</i>

1572
01:36:01,810 --> 01:36:04,680
<i>and plans to attend a variety of events.</i>
<i>并计划出席各种活动</i>

1573
01:36:05,350 --> 01:36:07,780
<i>In Hamburg, thousands of cheering Germans</i>
<i>在汉堡, 成千上万的德国人欢呼雀跃</i>

1574
01:36:07,810 --> 01:36:11,150
<i>welcome the Americans as they ready to disembark.</i>
<i>欢迎准备上岸的美国人</i>

1575
01:36:11,780 --> 01:36:13,370
<i>These amateur athletes</i>
<i>这些业余运动员</i>

1576
01:36:13,480 --> 01:36:15,670
<i>have sacrificed so much to represent their country, </i>
<i>他们为代表自己的国家做出了巨大牺牲</i>

1577
01:36:15,930 --> 01:36:18,860
<i>and as the opening of the Games is just days away, </i>
<i>还有几天奥运会就要开幕了</i>

1578
01:36:18,890 --> 01:36:20,580
<i>Americans at home and abroad</i>
<i>海内外的美国人</i>

1579
01:36:20,640 --> 01:36:23,800
<i>look forward to rooting for these dedicated athletes.</i>
<i>期待为这些敬业的运动员们加油助威</i>

1580
01:37:00,430 --> 01:37:02,060
Hi.
你好

1581
01:37:07,340 --> 01:37:08,330
All right.
好的

1582
01:37:12,410 --> 01:37:15,640
Get changed, we'll go look over the course.
换好衣服, 我们去看看航道

1583
01:37:23,050 --> 01:37:24,420
This is great.
这太棒了

1584
01:37:24,440 --> 01:37:25,380
Not bad.
还不错

1585
01:37:26,400 --> 01:37:28,700
- This'll do. - It's better than back home.
- 这就够了 - 比在老家强多了

1586
01:37:31,050 --> 01:37:32,080
<i>Heil Hitler.</i>
<i>希特勒万岁</i>

1587
01:37:32,260 --> 01:37:33,970
Remember the Alamo.
记住阿拉莫

1588
01:37:36,570 --> 01:37:38,110
Joe, opening ceremony.
乔, 开幕式

1589
01:37:38,130 --> 01:37:39,330
Come on, you're gonna be late.
快点 你要迟到了

1590
01:37:40,160 --> 01:37:41,700
I think I gotta skip.
我想我就不去了

1591
01:37:41,850 --> 01:37:43,220
I'm just too tired.
我太累了

1592
01:37:44,230 --> 01:37:46,000
Why, what's the problem, Don?
怎么了, 有什么问题吗, 唐？

1593
01:37:48,780 --> 01:37:50,210
Don doesn't feel so great.
唐感觉不太好

1594
01:38:07,830 --> 01:38:09,860
Go join the rest. I'll, uh... I'll stay.
去和其他人会合吧 我留下

1595
01:38:10,010 --> 01:38:13,380
I'll hang back. You need to walk with your team.
我来殿后 你得和你的团队一起走

1596
01:38:15,940 --> 01:38:17,210
Thanks, George.
谢谢你, 乔治

1597
01:38:19,610 --> 01:38:21,280
All right, get some rest.
好了, 休息吧

1598
01:38:21,710 --> 01:38:23,100
Try and eat somethin'.
吃点东西吧

1599
01:38:32,990 --> 01:38:34,720
<i>Ungarn.</i>
<i>匈牙利</i>

1600
01:38:50,270 --> 01:38:52,510
You're Jesse, right? Jesse Owens?
你是杰西, 对吧？杰西·欧文斯？

1601
01:38:52,710 --> 01:38:53,910
I am.
我是

1602
01:38:54,260 --> 01:38:56,120
You really the fastest man in the world?
你真的是世界上跑得最快的人吗？

1603
01:38:56,520 --> 01:38:58,190
- I don't know. - Folks around here say
- 我不知道 - 这里的人说

1604
01:38:58,220 --> 01:38:59,640
you're gonna win every race you're in.
你会赢下你参加的每一场比赛

1605
01:38:59,780 --> 01:39:01,140
Well, I hope so.
但愿如此

1606
01:39:01,300 --> 01:39:03,100
Show those Germans what for, all right?
给德国人点厉害瞧瞧, 好吗？

1607
01:39:03,480 --> 01:39:05,690
- No. - No?
- 不 - 不

1608
01:39:05,760 --> 01:39:07,100
Not the Germans.
不是给德国人

1609
01:39:07,990 --> 01:39:09,290
The folks back home.
是给家乡的父老乡亲的

1610
01:39:15,660 --> 01:39:17,830
<i>United States of America.
美利坚合众国</i>

1611
01:39:22,170 --> 01:39:23,670
<i>The Hungarian team
匈牙利队</i>

1612
01:39:23,810 --> 01:39:25,340
<i>offering their respect to the German leader.</i>
<i>向德国领导人表示敬意</i>

1613
01:39:25,840 --> 01:39:28,140
<i>And here come the Americans.</i>
<i>美国人来了</i>

1614
01:39:28,890 --> 01:39:31,690
<i>With no salute from the United States.</i>
<i>美国没有敬礼</i>

1615
01:39:32,940 --> 01:39:35,540
Sounds like the boys are making friends.
听起来孩子们正在交朋友

1616
01:39:39,890 --> 01:39:41,320
<i>All right, the winds are up.</i>
<i>好了, 起风了</i>

1617
01:39:41,360 --> 01:39:44,260
<i>That's good for us. You're protected in lane two.
这对我们有好处 你们在第二道不受直接影响</i>

1618
01:39:44,740 --> 01:39:46,310
Let all the other boats farther out
让其他更远的船

1619
01:39:46,330 --> 01:39:47,630
deal with the gusts.
去对付阵风吧

1620
01:39:47,840 --> 01:39:50,150
Bobby, the tighter you hold the line,
鲍比, 你越是紧守

1621
01:39:50,240 --> 01:39:51,480
the smoother the ride.
比赛就越平稳

1622
01:39:52,130 --> 01:39:53,690
Now, three prelims.
现在是三场预赛

1623
01:39:53,870 --> 01:39:56,890
The winner of each gets an automatic berth in the finals.
每场预赛的获胜者将自动获得总决赛的入场券

1624
01:39:56,970 --> 01:39:59,110
That is what you want. You want a day off
这就是你们想要的 休息一天

1625
01:39:59,210 --> 01:40:00,840
and let the other teams wear themselves out
让其他球队疲于奔命

1626
01:40:00,980 --> 01:40:02,040
with an extra race.
多赛一场

1627
01:40:02,180 --> 01:40:03,570
So, do not hold back.
所以, 不要保留

1628
01:40:03,600 --> 01:40:05,700
Great Britain's the team to watch in our heat.
英国队是我们这组值得关注的队伍

1629
