<i>Six minutes point eight seconds.</i>
<i>六分八秒</i>

1652
01:41:13,450 --> 01:41:14,950
<i>A new Olympic record!</i>
<i>新的奥运纪录！</i>

1653
01:41:15,060 --> 01:41:16,690
<i>The United States has won!</i>
<i>美国赢了！</i>

1654
01:41:19,240 --> 01:41:20,970
You all right? Hey, you know we won?
你还好吗？嘿, 你知道我们赢了吗？

1655
01:41:21,020 --> 01:41:23,320
- Don, are you okay? - You know we won, right? Huh?
- 唐, 你还好吗？- 你知道我们赢了, 对吧？嗯？

1656
01:41:23,460 --> 01:41:24,960
- Hey. - Come on. Come on.
- 嘿 - 来吧

1657
01:41:25,040 --> 01:41:26,040
<i>Good race.</i>
<i>精彩的比赛</i>

1658
01:41:26,060 --> 01:41:27,770
Olympic record's a nice start.
奥运纪录是个好的开始

1659
01:41:27,900 --> 01:41:30,330
But all that does is get us into the race that matters.
但这一切只是为了让我们进入真正重要的比赛

1660
01:41:30,410 --> 01:41:33,650
Nobody is gonna remember you set a record at a preliminary.
没有人会记得你在预赛中创下的记录

1661
01:41:34,760 --> 01:41:35,720
Now...
现在...

1662
01:41:36,420 --> 01:41:38,420
let's go see what we're up against.
让我们去看看我们要对付的是谁

1663
01:41:42,950 --> 01:41:43,940
Good job.
干得好

1664
01:41:44,580 --> 01:41:45,940
Way to go. Way to go.
干得好 干得好

1665
01:41:47,050 --> 01:41:48,420
Good work, boys.
干得好, 孩子们

1666
01:42:19,180 --> 01:42:20,710
Singles, doubles,
单人赛 双人赛

1667
01:42:21,360 --> 01:42:23,020
fours, they haven't lost a race yet.
四人赛 他们还没有输过一场

1668
01:42:30,700 --> 01:42:31,690
Fast.
快

1669
01:42:39,830 --> 01:42:41,030
Don, come on.
唐, 来吧

1670
01:42:42,270 --> 01:42:43,740
Hey, come on.
嘿, 走吧

1671
01:42:49,380 --> 01:42:50,580
You all right?
你没事吧？

1672
01:42:51,700 --> 01:42:52,930
Coach! Coach!
教练 教练！

1673
01:42:53,540 --> 01:42:56,280
- You okay? - Mm-hmm. I'm just worn out.
- 你还好吗？- 没事 我只是累坏了

1674
01:43:03,680 --> 01:43:05,610
Thank you, Doctor. Thanks for your help.
谢谢你 医生 谢谢你的帮助

1675
01:43:08,840 --> 01:43:09,930
What's the word?
怎么说？

1676
01:43:10,050 --> 01:43:11,710
Some kind of bug. They're not sure what.
某种虫子 他们不确定是什么

1677
01:43:11,730 --> 01:43:13,730
Right now, he's very dehydrated.
现在, 他脱水严重

1678
01:43:14,190 --> 01:43:15,280
He needs rest.
他需要休息

1679
01:43:15,310 --> 01:43:17,520
And y'all stay away from him for the next 24 hours.
接下来的24小时, 你们都离他远点

1680
01:43:17,640 --> 01:43:19,180
We can't afford losing anybody else.
我们不能再失去任何人了

1681
01:43:19,200 --> 01:43:20,370
What do you mean, "losing"?
你说 "失去" 是什么意思？

1682
01:43:20,940 --> 01:43:23,940
If he's still like this in two days, he's not racing.
如果两天后他还是这样, 他就不能参加比赛了

1683
01:43:29,220 --> 01:43:31,190
Lane assignments for the finals.
决赛航道分配

1684
01:43:40,510 --> 01:43:41,800
<i>You can't change the rules</i>
<i>你不能在比赛中间</i>

1685
01:43:41,830 --> 01:43:43,370
<i>in the middle of a competition!</i>
<i>改变规则</i>

1686
01:43:43,670 --> 01:43:46,170
The fastest qualifiers earn the favored lanes.
最快的预赛选手优先选择航道

1687
01:43:46,250 --> 01:43:47,730
That is the way it's always been.
一直就是这样

1688
01:43:47,820 --> 01:43:49,390
And we posted the best time,
我们创造了最好的记录

1689
01:43:49,470 --> 01:43:51,040
and you've gone and stuck us on the outside.
你却把我们困在外面

1690
01:43:51,100 --> 01:43:52,540
This was the lane formula the committee decided on.
这是奥委会决定的航道分配公式

1691
01:43:52,560 --> 01:43:53,910
When? Right after your squad
什么时候？就在你们队

1692
01:43:53,940 --> 01:43:55,430
posted the slowest qualifying time?
划出最慢的排位时间之后？

1693
01:43:55,460 --> 01:43:57,290
Be careful of your accusations, Coach Ulbrickson.
小心你的指控, 乌尔布里克森教练

1694
01:43:57,380 --> 01:43:59,550
You've seen the winds on that course and you know
你见过航道上的风, 你知道

1695
01:43:59,620 --> 01:44:01,470
there's a two-length disadvantage when it blows.
顶风时, 有两个长度的劣势

1696
01:44:01,490 --> 01:44:02,800
