我相信你的艇员们会处理好的

1697
01:44:02,820 --> 01:44:04,830
The forecasters expect a calm day.
天气预报预计今天会风平浪静

1698
01:44:08,160 --> 01:44:09,360
Well...
嗯...

1699
01:44:10,720 --> 01:44:11,720
We'll protest this.
我们对此表示抗议

1700
01:44:11,740 --> 01:44:13,540
Noted. And good luck.
记下了 祝你好运

1701
01:45:13,290 --> 01:45:15,860
All right. Listen up, boys.
好了 听好了 孩子们

1702
01:45:16,630 --> 01:45:19,400
It's a tough lane, so you gotta start quick.
这条航道很难走, 所以你们开始时得快点

1703
01:45:19,890 --> 01:45:21,690
You gotta keep them in sight.
必须让他们在你的视线范围内

1704
01:45:22,520 --> 01:45:24,840
That wind will be blocked for the last 500 meters.
最后 500 米那里 风会被挡住

1705
01:45:24,860 --> 01:45:26,120
And that's your shot.
这就是你们的机会

1706
01:45:26,200 --> 01:45:27,530
That's where you're gonna take 'em,
这就是你们拿下他们的地方

1707
01:45:27,670 --> 01:45:29,580
but only if you keep 'em in sight.
但前提是 你们得让他们保持在视线范围内

1708
01:45:29,920 --> 01:45:31,550
Listen, every one of those teams
听着, 每一支球队

1709
01:45:31,780 --> 01:45:34,040
have trained their whole lives for this moment.
为了这一刻, 他们训练了一辈子

1710
01:45:34,690 --> 01:45:36,230
They're all legacies.
它们都是富家子

1711
01:45:36,320 --> 01:45:37,620
We're not.
我们不是

1712
01:45:42,520 --> 01:45:44,490
Row for your country.
为了祖国

1713
01:45:45,160 --> 01:45:46,520
Row for each other.
为了彼此

1714
01:45:47,590 --> 01:45:49,680
Row for that one moment when everything
为了一切不利因素

1715
01:45:49,710 --> 01:45:52,290
that's stacked against you can take a back seat.
都退避三舍的那一刻

1716
01:45:58,800 --> 01:46:00,870
For what it's worth, I'm proud of you boys.
无论结果如何, 我都为你们感到骄傲

1717
01:46:05,990 --> 01:46:07,390
All right, push off.
好了, 出发吧

1718
01:46:15,120 --> 01:46:16,120
What?
什么？

1719
01:46:17,380 --> 01:46:18,580
Nothin'
没事

1720
01:46:32,310 --> 01:46:33,640
They might as well have stuck us
他们还不如把我们扔

1721
01:46:33,670 --> 01:46:35,230
out on the North Atlantic.
在北大西洋上

1722
01:46:45,190 --> 01:46:46,750
<i>Thousands of people are taking their seats, </i>
<i>成千上万的人正在入座</i>

1723
01:46:46,820 --> 01:46:48,650
<i>gathered for the Men's Eights finals.</i>
<i>男子组八人决赛</i>

1724
01:46:48,890 --> 01:46:50,590
<i>The world's six best rowing teams</i>
<i>世界上最好的六支赛艇队</i>

1725
01:46:50,620 --> 01:46:52,390
<i>in one last race for the gold.</i>
<i>为金牌进行最后的角逐</i>

1726
01:46:52,650 --> 01:46:54,260
<i>Germany, Italy, Hungary
<i>德国 意大利 匈牙利</i>

1727
01:46:54,320 --> 01:46:56,790
<i>Germany has taken gold in singles, doubles, and fours, </i>
<i>德国在单人 双人和四人比赛中摘得金牌</i>

1728
01:46:56,860 --> 01:46:58,460
<i>and they're looking for a sweep.</i>
<i>他们正在追求大满贯</i>

1729
01:46:58,600 --> 01:47:01,270
<i>Switzerland, Great Britain, and the United States
<i>瑞士 英国和美国</i>

1730
01:47:01,330 --> 01:47:02,840
<i>round out the six.</i>
<i>位列前六</i>

1731
01:47:02,870 --> 01:47:04,700
<i>The boys from Washington so close</i>
<i>来自华盛顿的男孩们如此接近于</i>

1732
01:47:04,730 --> 01:47:07,160
<i>to bringing an Olympic title back to Seattle.</i>
<i>将奥运冠军带回西雅图</i>

1733
